The Federal Capital Territory Administration has announced the death of one coronavirus patient in Abuja. The announcement was made by the FCTA in a tweet via its Twitter account on Tuesday. According to the Administration, 18 new cases of the viral infection was also recorded. The tweet reads “18 NEW CASES, 21 DISCHARGED & 1 DEATH IN THE FCT. “Summary of COVID19FCT as at August 10th, 2020. “Total number of confirmed cases: 4485. “Total number of active cases: 3325. “1112 Patients have been discharged with 48 deaths recorded. “Residents are urged to stay safe.”